ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: Jai Bhairv Welfare Society is a non-profit community based organization working towards peopole empowerment, education and livelihood promotion. JBWS aspires to improve the living conditions of the poor and marginalized by adopting strategies & Technology through community initiative, participation and sensitization. Founded in 2009, the organization has worked among the villagers and boarder area of Rajasthan. People self-help groups have been taken as the base for all interventions and livelihood activities enabling them to contribute towards mainstream development process. The main objectives of the Project are: To strengthen the income-generating capacity of the unemployed youth, with a special focus on rural unemployed youth. To facilitate the groups to develop their managerial and technical capabilities so that they manage their micro enterprise efficiently. To establish effective linkages between the Rural Youth and all major support organizations by creating a single platform for communication. To provide market information and develop the capacity of the Rural Artisans for conducting market research. To promote community based organizations at grassroots level for sustainable development in rural and coastal areas. Currently, both companies share the same management, operating address and human resources.

ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: Kinkini is primarily a cultural organization with great potential to promote, propagate and dissemination of Indian art, culture in its different facets.the organization organizes large number of quality programmes, involving the classical artists, puppeteers, Dramatists but tribal and folk artist too. the main activities of the organization is to produce production, cultural studies, research, conduct workshops, performances, organize seminars, training on classical and folk art, music, dance, theatre, puppetry, etc. to revive vanishing art forms. Kinkini embarked on objects of organizing rich tradition of GURU SHISHYA Parampara. The organization organizes workshops for special children and brings them to the main stream. Kinkini conducts art in education programme in rural areas to create interest for formal education. Kinkini regularly perform street theatre on social issues. To achieve all these objects the organization conducting every year workshops, dance ballets, folk dance production, seminars, research on tribal musical instruments, children theatre and also regularly working to revive vanishing art forms since 1993. so far the organization worked on several projects, art in education programme in 40 villages, 15, kathak dance workshops, several dance performance, ballets, puppetry, workshops on puppetry,folk dances , drama, folk singing,etc.Conducted seminars and performances tribal art form like Gavri,Pabu ji ki Phad, puppetry, tribal music etc. Research on tribal musical instruments of Rajasthan and many many shows of street theatre. kinkini has performed all over India. above all the organizations aim is to develop ways and means through which the basic cultural and aesthetic sensibilities of the people remain active and dynamic.
